								<span class="text-slate-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform duration-200">
									<svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
								</span>
							</summary>
							<p class="mt-3 text-xs sm:text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
								To put an expiry date on a record, navigate to the Secura dashboard, click 'Add Document', and write the document title or domain. Choose its target category, use the calendar picker to specify the exact calendar date of expiration, and write any secondary notes or credentials. The application will immediately calculate the remaining timeframe and display a status indicator.
							</p>
